It's

00:03:51.590 --> 00:03:53.548
JOHN DOLHUN: Oh, my
goodness, I can see myself.

00:04:07.070 --> 00:04:11.050
Well, this is a real
workout, I'll tell you.

00:04:15.660 --> 00:04:20.010
So what we've created
here is a beautiful silver

00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:20.849
mirrored flask.

00:04:25.029 --> 00:04:26.070
JESSICA: So look at that.

00:04:26.070 --> 00:04:29.670
Dr. Dolhun has created a
beautiful silver mirror.

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:31.830
It almost looks like a
Christmas tree ornament.

00:04:31.830 --> 00:04:35.070
And a silver ornament could,
in fact, be made this way.

00:04:35.070 --> 00:04:36.810
So here's what's happening.

00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:38.940
Electrons from
here, the glucose,

00:04:38.940 --> 00:04:42.610
get transferred to the silver,
reducing it to silver zero.

00:04:47.510 --> 00:04:49.850
Silver zero is
insoluble in water.

00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:55.160
It's just silver metal,
and it's precipitating out

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:58.310
on the inside of the flask,
forming the beautiful silver

00:04:58.310 --> 00:05:00.080
mirror that we see.

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:03.680
Now, this process is
called "reduction."

00:05:03.680 --> 00:05:05.510
And whenever
something is reduced,

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:07.730
something else is oxidized.

00:05:07.730 --> 00:05:10.970
So the glucose must
be getting oxidized.

00:05:10.970 --> 00:05:12.110
It becomes this.

00:05:15.960 --> 00:05:18.550
An oxygen was added here.

00:05:18.550 --> 00:05:22.240
Now, this process is similar
to metabolism in our bodies.

00:05:22.240 --> 00:05:24.700
We remove electrons
from the sugar we eat,

00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:27.880
and transfer them to the
oxygen that we breathe.

00:05:27.880 --> 00:05:30.400
In a reduction reaction
like mirror, mirror,

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:32.410
there might be energy released.

00:05:32.410 --> 00:05:35.830
In your body, this energy is
harnessed in chemical bonds,

00:05:35.830 --> 00:05:37.780
stored for later.

00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:41.320
The point of Tollens' Test was
not to produce silver mirrors,

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:44.200
although a similar reaction
is used for that today.

00:05:44.200 --> 00:05:47.750
The point was to distinguish
between two types of sugars--

00:05:47.750 --> 00:05:51.190
ones containing aldehyde
and ones containing ketones.

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:52.030
Let me draw those.

00:05:57.130 --> 00:05:59.050
The difference is
that in an aldehyde,

00:05:59.050 --> 00:06:02.740
the carbon is connected to
a hydrogen. And in a ketone,

00:06:02.740 --> 00:06:05.650
the carbon is connected
to another carbon.

00:06:05.650 --> 00:06:08.110
Aldehydes are more
reactive than ketones,

00:06:08.110 --> 00:06:10.360
so they will react
with the silver ions,

00:06:10.360 --> 00:06:12.412
while the ketones will not.

